==English==
===Etymology===
Italian or Latin ''cantilena''.

===Pronunciation===
[[IPA]]: /kæntɪ'leɪnə/

===Noun===
'''cantilena'''
# a vocal melody or instrumental passage in a smooth, lyrical style
#:*'''1964''': He played a lazy tune that sinuated from C sharp down to G natural and back again.  Astonishing that he could flute so lazy a '''cantilena''' while chasing nymphs. — Anthony Burgess, ''The Eve of St Venus''